{"parentUuid":"976e37c7-c56d-4b3d-9102-0cbf2f4c3da6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01QfyoMXQ4vAmCjpMkHPjnok","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VrMRP9SZvewjWDjNK8y9e8","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/CHANGELOG.md","old_string":"The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/),\nand this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n\n## [0.4.2] - 2026-04-30","new_string":"The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/),\nand this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n\n## [0.4.3] - 2026-05-07\n\nBootstrap robustness and observability. Batched bootstrap now self-tunes\nunder heavy regions (early-aborts doomed pushes, sizes subdivisions from\nobserved bytes, recombines after small packs), gains a `topo` strategy\nfor merge-heavy histories, and surfaces live per-side throughput.\n\n### Added\n\n- `--bootstrap-strategy=topo` for merge-heavy repos. The default\n  first-parent walk caps sub-pack granularity at first-parent steps; the\n  topo strategy walks every reachable commit in deterministic\n  topological order (Kahn's algorithm with hash-tie-broken queue for\n  stable resume), so batched bootstrap can place sub-pack boundaries\n  inside side-branch ancestry. Plumbed through `bootstrap`, `sync`,\n  `replicate`, and `plan`, and through the public `gitsync` API\n  ([#41](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/41))\n- `--progress` for a live two-row throughput region across `sync`,\n  `replicate`, `bootstrap`, and `fetch`. Per-side rolling-window rate,\n  hostname-aware labels, and bootstrap pack subdivision surfaced inline\n  as `(pack 3/8)` / `(pushing pack)` / `(pushing tags)`. Auto-suppressed\n  off-TTY. `--stats` gains an end-of-run throughput summary, and\n  sideband `\\r` progress is rendered above the ticker without trampling\n  it ([#37](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/37))\n- Per-subcommand `--help`. The CLI moved to cobra, so each subcommand\n  prints its own usage and bare `git-sync` lists subcommands on stdout\n  instead of dumping the full usage block as an error. Flag names, env\n  vars, positional args, and JSON output are unchanged\n  ([#35](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/35))\n- README cover image and embedded demo videos for `git-sync plan` and\n  `git-sync sync` ([#30](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/30),\n  [#31](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/31))\n\n### Changed\n\n- Batched bootstrap aborts doomed pushes around 5% in instead of waiting\n  for the server's body-limit rejection. The pack reader is wrapped in a\n  streaming `packfile.Scanner` exposing `ObjectsSent` / `TotalObjects`,\n  which the retry loop uses to project final pack size and bail early.\n  Per-object calibration now divides by the observed object count\n  rather than the full pack count, and the subdivision factor uses the\n  projection rather than raw `sentBytes`. Failed retries cost ~5% of\n  pack size instead of 100%, and subdivision converges in 1–2 rounds\n  instead of 6+ on blob-heavy repos\n  ([#40](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/40))\n- Post-rejection subdivision uses observed pack bytes instead of always\n  halving the checkpoint count. When the server cuts the upload off\n  mid-stream (`sent_bytes ≈ limit`, the common reverse-proxy 413), the\n  factor escalates to 4× to converge in a single round; otherwise 2×.\n  Each 413 also ratchets the running bytes-per-object estimate up so\n  later sub-packs are pre-emptively split. Falls back to legacy halving\n  when no signal is available\n  ([#38](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/38))\n- Batched bootstrap recombines upcoming checkpoints when consecutive\n  packs underuse the target body limit. After a successful push, the\n  executor drops up to 8 upcoming checkpoints so the next pack lands\n  near half the target limit (drop count is `log2(target/2 / sent)`),\n  recovering pack granularity after a heavy region forced fine\n  subdivision. Already-pushed checkpoints are also declared as fetch\n  `have`s on subsequent rounds, so topo-ordered merge commits don't\n  re-send side-branch ancestry that was already transferred\n  ([#42](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/42))\n- Relay-only syncs skip the upfront `FetchToStore`. The incremental\n  relay already streams the source pack to the target itself, so the\n  prior upfront fetch was paying for the source pack twice. The\n  materialized fallback now lazy-fetches the source closure only when\n  it actually needs the graph (force, prune, divergent refs)\n  ([#34](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/34))\n\n### Fixed\n\n- Sync into targets that share reachability with the source. The\n  materialized walker now treats missing top-level and transitive\n  objects as implicitly already present, since the source prunes its\n  closure when target refs are passed as `have`s. Incremental relay\n  accepts branch creates (including mixed create+update batches) and\n  `no-thin` targets instead of falling through to materialized. Opaque\n  5xx responses surface diagnostic headers (`Cf-Ray`, `Server`,\n  `X-Request-Id`, …) so an upstream operator has something to act on\n  ([#33](https://github.com/entireio/git-sync/pull/33))\n\n## [0.4.2] - 2026-04-30"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3628,"cache_read_input_tokens":57433,"output_tokens":2331,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3628,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":2331,"cache_read_input_tokens":57433,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3628,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":